{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Provides a circular "quick menu" for commonly-used actions, similar to how weapons are selected in many FPS games.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Instructions:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 - Bind the script to a key\line
- Hold the key down, a window will open\line
- Use the mouse to choose menu options and click on actions\line
- Let the key go when you're done, and the window will close\line
\line
- Right-click the window to enter Setup mode\line
    - You can release the keyboard key; the window will stay open\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Setup mode: - Click and hold the left mouse button on a menu option to edit it - Buttons can be relabelled and assigned any Action ID you want - Alternatively, set the action to e.g. 'menu 12' to create a new submenu -1 - reserved for script settings. Don't use it. 0 - the one you see when the script starts 1-8 - the eight default submenus - You should be able to make as many submenus as you want.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 - Press F1 to access color settings; all are RGBA, 0-255\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 See the forum thread for further documentation, reporting bugs, etc.\par}
}

